fees.name: Fixed rate lock fee
fees.additionalInfo: 0.15% of the original Fixed Rate loan amount. Payable to secure the fixed interest rate on a fixed rate loan for 90 days from the date this fee is received (this date is also referred to as the fixed rate date quoted). This fee is not refundable.

fees.name: Break costs
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if at any time before the fixed interest period expires. You make additional repayments above the minimum required payments exceeding $10,000 for each 12 month period within a fixed interest period; or You repay all of the money owing under the facility during any fixed interest period before it is due; or We agree to change your annual percentage rate during your fixed interest period (this includes a change to your annual percentage ratedue to a change to your repayment type [principal andinterest or interest only] or a change to your loan purpose [owner occupied or investment]). Break costs can be substantial. The amount which is our estimate of loss (if any) resulting from the relevant event.  A 12 month period is defined as the time from the date the fixed interest period commenced to the initial anniversary of that date and each consecutive anniversary thereafter until the fixed interest period expires. Refer to your Loan Conditions for more information.

fees.name: Discharge fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when we are requested to discharge all securities. Customers also pay the actual solicitors' or mortgage processing servicers' costs, which include,for example, search fees and postage, valuation costs if applicable and any applicable Government fees, which may vary from state to state.

fees.name: Application fee
fees.additionalInfo: Processing fee for loan application payable at settlement

fees.name: Payment dishonour fees
fees.additionalInfo: You may be charged a fee by an external bank or financial institution for a transaction relating to your loan (eg. if a payment to your loan made from another bank is dishonoured, the other bank may charge you a fee).

fees.name: Cheque or electronic withdrawal dishonour fee
fees.additionalInfo: When a cheque or electronic withdrawal from your account is dishonoured

fees.name: Cheque deposit or electronic payment dishonour
fees.additionalInfo: When a cheque deposited to your account is dishonoured, or an electronic payment initiated from your account is sent back from a financial institution

fees.name: Bank cheque fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to: issue a bank cheque, provide a replacement bank cheque for one previously issued, repurchase a bank cheque you no longer require,arrange to make a bank cheque available for you to collect from a Westpac branch. Interest payable on the bank cheque amount from the day the request is processed by us.

fees.name: Deposit special clearance fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to expedite the clearance of a cheque deposited to your account

fees.name: Duplicate statement fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request a copy of a previously provided statement to be sent to you by mail

fees.name: Telegraphic transfer fee - deposits
fees.additionalInfo: When funds are transferred to your account (by SWIFT or telegraphic transfer) from a bank in Australia or overseas (in Australian dollars or a foreign currency)

fees.name: Telegraphic transfer fee - withdrawals
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to transfer funds from your account (by SWIFT) to a bank in Australia (in Australian dollars). When you request us to transfer funds from your account (by telegraphic transfer) to an overseas bank (in Australian dollars or a foreign currency).

fees.name: Transaction trace fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you request us to investigate and trace a transaction

fees.name: Audit certificate fee
fees.additionalInfo: When you or an auditor request an audit certificate for your account

features.additionalValue: Redraw of repaid principal above minimum required is available
features.additionalInfo: Redraw applies to variable rate loans only. Redraw extra funds you deposit whenever you like, with no withdrawal fees. You can redraw your extra funds using online banking, our mobile apps, BankPhone and BankAssist.

features.additionalValue: Access is available to online banking features for the product
